rComments: I thoroughly enjoyed Prof Dumas' lectures, as he was always extremely passionate and enthusiastic about the material. He was very respectful and didn't talk down to his students, even telling us we could just refer to him as "Alex". I really hope I get to have him as a prof again, by far my favourite prof that I've had in my first 2 years of uni.
Nice guy, not a good prof. Rambles on during his lectures and you leave feeling as though you didn't learn anything at all. Midterm was hard.

He seems nice and knowledgable, but lectures are kind of unclear. I was told this was a bird course but that was 100% wrong. He makes this a very dense course with a lot of material, all questions are short answer with a word limit, makes it hard to get your thoughts out. Very harsh grading scheme, 35% midterm, 30% group project, and 35% final.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: Most students appeared to skip lectures because they were boring and usually not helpful- most of the time Dumas was unclear with his words and regularly went over the allotted time period for classes with little regard for respecting his students time. He has also been known to make belittling comments to students. Overall, would not recommend.

I skipped nearly every lecture and barely sudied the day of the midterm and final and still finished with a B+. The exam questions were fair, but the word count severely limited the students ability to demonstrate knowledge (a 30 mark question and you could use 100 words to answer). Uses outdated & inappropriate terms- this is unacceptable.
Interesting/good prof but he's a tough grader. Don't mistake this class as a GPA booster.

He's a very good teacher. He knows his content very well and communicates it very efficiently. The powerpoints are sometimes overwhelming because of how much there is to learn, understand and memorize but if you start you're studying early, you should be just fine for the exams. I definitely recommend him!

Dumas is a good prof. He explains the material very well except in some rare cases he was a little confusing like with the Supply and Demand diagram. Showing up to class and taking good notes is must since there is very little information on his powerpoint. His exams were all short answers so studying well is a must, but I found them very fair.

Alex is one of the most fun profs I've had in a a long time. Genuinely nice, helpful and cute. The content and lectures were very interesting. Make sure to attend class and take good notes, as most of what he says appears on the exam and not in the lecture slides.
had for history of sport.

Un de mes profs préférés à date dans mon BAC, il est clair lorsqu'il explique, les slides sont faciles à suivre (je conseille de les imprimer pour les remplir à la main en classe). Les examens sont très "fair" et il faut comprendre la matière. Très facile de poser des questions en classe et même après le cours.
Very knowledgeable and clear. Strict with grading and papers though.

Alex is a great teacher. He is strong in his field, you might want to meet with him and ask questions to make sure you understand everything. He's also able to guide you and help you through the semester. A great teacher with A LOT OF KNOWLEDGE. Yes, he has an accent. But try speaking another language first, then critizise. :) Merci Alex!

I took the sociology of sport course in french and LOVED it. He is super passionate about his subject, he gives numerous examples, and his exams are very fair. You definitely need to attend class as he doesn`t have a lot of info on his slides, but the subject is very interesting. Definitely recommend!
Very nice teacher. Very clear and makes his subject interesting. He likes having discussions with students as well as helping them at any time. One of the best teachers I've had!
Not sure what everyone is talking about. He's very nice, funny, helpful. Definitely a good prof and cares about his students. Pretty cute too.
Talk too much, but was clear

Not an overly difficult class; seems intimidating and he even says the course is difficult. You do have to work fairly hard to get a good grade in the course but his exams are really fair and if you narrow your sociological approach in the article and have good sources you'll do well (try to respect the word limit though).
Sometimes hard to understand but overall a really nice and good teacher

The class is soo boring, and he doesnt make it any easier. He wont post the lecture notes till like a week after the class. Hes rude, not helpful and disorganized. He's a "discussion" prof and gets mad if you answer wrong or dont answer at all. We barely used the text, and none of it was on the exam, no point buying the text. just read the notes

C'est what?  One of the worst classes I have ever taken - literally bored me to sleep!  I can not believe it was a perequisite.  The prof barely speaks english and it's noticeable that he can't get what he's thinking into words in the first 3 minutes of the very first class!  Nice guy, but should stick to teaching in french 4 now!
Is class sucks, and he doesnt have any skills to teach...too weird for me!
Asks too many questions and gets mad when someone answers with the wrong answer. Bad accent, was really hard to understand.
Same as above. Can't stand going to that class.
Asks way to many questions in class, lectures seem like the biggest waste of time, repeats himself, gets off topic, looks for specific answers from the class..overall pretty crappy
